text:
I feel like this year's rewind did capture some good points from 2018. But there were a lot of things that happened this year other than fortnite and k-pop. Though I do think those were big things, and they should've been added, there were really huge things that happened this year other than those. And I think why everyone did not like this year's rewind. 

Youtube rewind is about looking back on the year, and what happened and what was big. And who was big. Shane Dawson's series were huge this year, and got millions of views. This is one thing that I've seen people be mad about. Because Shane Dawson wasn't mentioned, nor was his series. 

Last year's Rewind had a little bit of seriousness to it. And I feel like people should've addressed what happened with Logan Paul this year. Even the event with Logan and KSI. 

Other people I feel like should've been mentioned was MrBeast ,for all his donations, James Charles for his general popularity this year, Game Theory for the huge nine hour mental illness livestream, and Pewdiepie, because he is still the biggest YouTuber. 

Last year's rewind also had memes, challenges, and references in it. I feel like things like TicToc, Dr. Phil, and Tidepods were big things this year. And references, phrases, or quotes could've been included too. 

Overall, this is why I think people don't like this year's rewind. If you disagree, cool. If you agree, cool. This is just what I think. 

P.S. If I misspelled anything, my apologies. I did not look it over and my phone keyboard is tiny :pÔªø

text: Aaaah It's Rewind time. If I controlled Rewind I would want Fortnite and Marques Brownlee. Is this what you wanted? You know who I would have asked for? Quit horsing around. Play me some of that jumping music. Did you say jumping music? Jumping music? Everybody! Off! Not even a thank you?! Is that Marques? I want Liza Yeaaaaaahhhh!!!! So guys, apparently we control Rewind this year. Y'all we can do whatever we want. What do we do? There's one thing this video needs. K-pop! Can I have a Royal Wedding? Yeah, but you're marrying Bongo Cat. Wait, what? Rewind needs more science. Can we do an experiment? I love that. Melting lipstick. ¬†I want to eat something. Mukbang! Yes, let's do it in Korea! Gallop, what do you want? Marshmello needs to be in this video. Who is Marshmello?How about yodeling kid? With Adam Rippon! Guys, let's do the In My Feelings challenge. Right! I love this song! Let's hear the remix! Wait, wait, wait. Hold on, hold on. You know who really needs to be in this Rewind video? Everyone who managed to do something bigger than themselves this year. Found a way to help the causes that matter to them most. To everyone who proved it's ok to talk about mental health this year. Showing our viewers that it's ok to go through tough times like that. It takes a lot of bravery to be that vulnerable and I'm so proud of this community I think this year's Rewind should celebrate the fierce, fabulous and empowering art of drag. I want to see all of you be your own kind of beautiful. And to those people who have raised money in the field of education. Can we also give a moment to Asian representation in entertainment this year? Major strides were made. And to the people who put aside their differences. Yeah, and created something really special. Here's to all women in 2018 for finding their voices. It's nice seeing how women grew and were empowered. Can we give a moment to working moms? Let's do it! To everyone who taught, or learned, something new this year. ¬†And to all the refugees and anyone looking for a home. All of us should send a toast to the kids who follow their dreams. I want to thank the whole community that always supports during our best and worst. We are a family, we are a team. Family is everything. I want to give a moment to everyone who supported me when I got sick. All of the comments and messages I got made me feel like I wasn't alone. We're forgetting something. text:
The Love-Hate story of me and Youtube Rewind 2018:
When I watched YR18 for the first time, I thought it was the best video I had ever seen. I liked the video immediately. Then, I went down to the comment section and found out that it was in fact the extreme opposite. In order to prove my love for YR18, I went back to every single YR and re-wound (from 2017-2010). By the glory of YouTube god, after watchin all the YR's I understood my sin . I came back here and disliked the video, thus ending our love story! 

And in my opinion, the best YR is YR2012!Ôªø

author: Mee June

text:
I AM SO DISAPPOINTED by this year's YTR. It could've been so much better. We, the YT community expected more. We expected more Vibrancy, color, life, and depth. you barely even scratched the surface of the iceberg that was 2018. I came for YTR, and what I got was a skit. It's fine to put it in the beginning and end but do NOT drag the skit throughout the video. You missed out on so many YouTubers and so many things that happened in  2018. There were some YouTubers that deserved way more recognition than some others in this. It just felt rushed.



You missed out on some very important highlights, KSI vs Logan Paul, T-Series vs PewDiePie ( though I concede that might not be appropriate, at least PewDiePie). You did not include singers and their songs that made 2018 2018, like Ariana Grande, Brendon Urie, Cardi B(bring her, and not just her songs), Shawn Mendes, Post Malone, Camila Cabello, Dua Lipa, and many more. What about KPOP? BTS? EXO? Sunmi? BLACKPINK? These were some the biggest KPop groups this year, specifically BTS and I fail to understand how they're not here. 



You missed out on Tristan Paredes, Slime, Shane Dawson, Fortnite vs PUBG(though I hardly think that should be included), JoJo Siwa, the Art community, Joana Ceddia, and so much more, not to mention all the memes and meme references. Where were all the YouTubers? There should've been more of them, and the people that did come were very irrelevant to many people, and I can assure you that people wouldn't have known many of the YouTubers you brought along. 



At the end of the day, we want a YTR, not a bunch of people talking about what they want in a YTR and how they want to control it. SHOW IT TO US. We want a sorta music video mashup, with everyone and everything who made this year good, NOT, A SKIT. Please, for all our sakes, make the next year's YTR better. Remember YTR 2k16? It was so good. This year was not. This year was something else entirely. I still have hope for the next year, so don't let us down.Ôªø

author: EnderLT

text: This year's rewind included a lot of great people. Most of the creators that I know on here I genuinely like, and there are a lot of really good, but not well known youtubers in here who wanted to get there faces out, and seeing them brought a smile to my face. However what started as a possibly fun parody of this year's events quickly spiraled into a cringy, poorly executed mash up of a bunch of cringy memes that, by the end of the year where so overused they were beyond dead and not even a skeleton of there former self. This could have been great, and adding a section of fuffiling the comments wishes was a good idea, but the problem is that the YouTube community tends to joke by making up ideas that seem decent at first, but when put into action, becomes a massive cringe-fest that nobody wanted in the first place. All in all, this is almost justifiably the worst thing on YouTube.Ôªø
